National Unemployment Insurance (UI) Benefits Study:  A comprehensive research study that examines:
o Changes in the labor market, population, and economy pertinent to the UI program;
o Changes in UI program outcomes, particularly duration of benefit receipt;
o Detailed characteristics of who does and does not receive UI benefits;
o Patterns of lifetime UI benefit receipt;
o The role of unemployment insurance in macro-economic stabilization; and
o The effectiveness of Reemployment Eligibility Assessments (REA) in nine state-specific projects.
